The concept of interchangable parts is one of the best ideas that mankind has ever conceived. # This sounds like a thesis in an argumentative essay
Without it, manufaturing would be slow and inconsistent. 
More critically, repairs would take a very long time 
as each broken part would have to be specially re-manufactured for the 
single broken product at hand. 
Without interchangable parts, engineering would be much more difficult-- 
if not impossible--as there would be no consistency or convention
between different groups of engineers. 
# Add clincher sentence/call to action if indeed argumentative essay
